  "title": "Part Time Clinic Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Part-Time Clinic Assistant (with Experience)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>- Only for mornings from 8.30am to 12.30pm</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>· Registration of patients, reception duties, dispensing medications and payment collections</p>\n<p>· Attend to phone calls, schedule appointment and send reminders to patients for chronic medication follow-up</p>\n<p>· Handle administration and documentation of referrals, lab tests and radiology services</p>\n<p>· Inventory check, medicines order and replenishing of medicines</p>\n<p>· Any other admin duties and responsibilities as assigned by Doctor or Clinic Manager</p>\n<p>· General housekeeping of clinic</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>· Previous experience as a Clinic Assistant</p>\n<p>· Minimum GCE N/O level qualifications</p>\n<p>· Basic computer skills</p>\n<p>· Familiar with clinic workflow and system (Clinic Assist CMS)</p>\n<p>· Positive, self-motivated and customer-service orientated</p>\n<p>· English and dialects speaking is essential</p>\n<p>· Able to work independently</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Clinic Details:</strong></p>\n<p>GP clinic within 5mins walking distance from Outram MRT</p>\n<p>Clinic is closed on Wed, Sat &amp; Public holidays</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Employment:</strong></p>\n<p>Part-time position</p>\n<p>Note: Only shortlisted candidates (with experience) will be contacted.</p>\n<p><br></p>",
